	<LINE>Incorporated therewith is</LINE>
	<LINE>THE GLASGOW FIFESHIRE SOCIETY.</LINE>
	<LINE>Instituted in 1759.</LINE>
	<LINE>Patron, William Baird, Esq., of Elie; president,</LINE>
	<LINE>Professor R. Berry; late president, W. Shaw, Esq.;</LINE>
	<LINE>vice-presidents, Thomas Marr, George Younger, and</LINE>
	<LINE>Eben. Barclay ; treasurer, W. R. Crombie ; secretary,</LINE>
	<LINE>J. C. Reid ; directors, for Fife, Messrs. Alex. Hogg,</LINE>
	<LINE>John Renton, M. Swan, William Alexander, James</LINE>
	<LINE>Butters, Thos. Hodge, Jas. Bain, John M'Intosh, and</LINE>
	<LINE>Geo. Rodger; for Kinross, Messrs. Wm. Blackwood,</LINE>
	<LINE>Wm. Wright, and Andrew D. Dixon ; for Clack-</LINE>
	<LINE>mannan, Messrs. Alexander Bennett, Thomas Izat,</LINE>
	<LINE>and James M'Gregor.</LINE>
	<LINE>The principal object of this society is to afford</LINE>
	<LINE>pecuniary aid to indigent natives, or widows, or chil-</LINE>
	<LINE>dren of natives, of these counties resident in or near</LINE>
	<LINE>Glasgow. The subscription of £1 Is. per annum for</LINE>
	<LINE>four years, or £4 4s. in one sum, constitutes mem-</LINE>
	<LINE>bership to parties eligible by connection with any of</LINE>
	<LINE>these counties; and gentlemen willing to be enrolled</LINE>
	<LINE>are respectfully solicited to communicate with the</LINE>
	<LINE>treasurer or secretary of the society, or any of the</LINE>
	<LINE>directors. Office, 217 West George Street.</LINE>
