	<LINE>THE GRAND ANTIQUITY SOCIETY</LINE>
	<LINE>OF GLASGOW.</LINE>
	<LINE>Instituted 16th November, 1756.</LINE>
	<LINE>The objects of this society are the relief of its</LINE>
	<LINE>members in infirmity or old age, and to secure a pro-</LINE>
	<LINE>vision to the widows of members iu indigent circum-</LINE>
	<LINE>stances. Persons eligible for admission to the society</LINE>
	<LINE>are burgesses, who are also the sons and grandsons</LINE>
	<LINE>either by the father's or mother's side of burgesses.</LINE>
	<LINE>The entry-money is £2 3s. Gd., excepting that for</LINE>
	<LINE>the sons and sons-in-law of members, who are admitted</LINE>
	<LINE>upon payment of the sum of £1 2s. 6d.</LINE>
